title: The Lord's My Shepherd
author: W. Whittingham; F. Rous
music: Jessie Seymour Irvine (1836-1887); Harmony by David Grant

v1: The Lord's my Shepherd, I'll not want;
He makes me down to lie
In pastures green; He leadeth me
v2: My soul He doth restore again,
And me to walk doth make
E'en for His own name's sake.
v3: Yea, though I walk in death's dark vale,
Yet will I fear no ill;
For Thou art with me, and Thy rod
v4: My head Thou dost with oil anoint,
v5: Goodness and mercy all my life
